Class AFSwinxConnection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tomscz.afswinx.rest.connection.AFSwinxConnection

  • public class AFSwinxConnection
extends java.lang.Object
    This class holds information which are necessary to get model or data and post them. Based on this are created concrete connectors.

      • AFSwinxConnection

        public AFSwinxConnection(java.lang.String address,
                 int port,
                 java.lang.String parameters)
        Constructor to create connection.
        Parameters:
        address - end point without protocol ex: localhost, toms-cz.com, google.com
        port - port in which service available.
        parameters - url parameters if service is available on localhost:8080/rest/personService then parameter are /rest/personService include slash, or localhost:8080/AFServer/rest/personService then parameter is /AFserver/rest/personService

      • AFSwinxConnection

        protected AFSwinxConnection()
        This constructor is protected because its used in ConnectionParser. It's easily use set method then hold all variables in memory. Default content and header type is application.json from HeaderType.
